<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFC8FFE3FF6BFBB1FD28FADE" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC8FFE3FF6BFBB1FC15FB1E" blockId="18.[151,1127,1111,1422]" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FF6BFBB1FEBBFBDE" bold="true" box="[151,261,1111,1134]" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC8FFE3FEF5FBB1FE06FBDE" author="BOHEMAN" box="[265,440,1111,1134]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
explicitly described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC8FFE3FD72FBB1FCD5FBDE" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[654,875,1111,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobiliata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FD72FBB1FCD5FBDE" box="[654,875,1111,1134]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">Coptocycla nobiliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single specimen. I also assume that 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC8FFE3FEA8FB91FDA6FB3E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[340,536,1143,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="briseis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FEA8FB91FDA6FB3E" box="[340,536,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">Coptocycla briseis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a single specimen according to the original description, due to its not fully sclerotized elytra and unusual colouration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC8FFE3FF49FB51FD28FADE" blockId="18.[151,1127,1111,1422]" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC8FFE3FF49FB51FEF0FB7E" author="SPAETH" box="[181,334,1207,1230]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref51203" refString="SPAETH F. 1926: Monographie der zu Gruppe der Coptocyclitae gehorigen amerikanischen Cassidinen (Col.): I. Die Gattungen mit gekammten Klauen. Supplementa Entomologica 13: 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1926">SPAETH (1926)</bibRefCitation>
studied a specimen compared with the type of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC8FFE3FCB1FB51FC0AFB7E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[845,948,1207,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="briseis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FCB1FB51FC0AFB7E" box="[845,948,1207,1230]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">C. briseis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by G. E. Bryant and concluded that it is close to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC8FFE3FDF8FB31FD39FB5E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[516,647,1239,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobiliata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FDF8FB31FD39FB5E" box="[516,647,1239,1262]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">C. nobiliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing only in the sparser punctation of elytra. I have studied the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC8FFE3FE5FFB11FDBEFABE" box="[419,512,1271,1294]" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC8FFE3FDDFFB11FD36FABE" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[547,648,1271,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="briseis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FDDFFB11FD36FABE" box="[547,648,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">C. briseis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as the specimen compared by Bryant and both are teneral and not fully sclerotized. As a result, the punctation of elytra artificially appears sparser and finer than in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC8FFE3FE08FAD1FDCDFAFE" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[500,627,1335,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobiliata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FE08FAD1FDCDFAFE" box="[500,627,1335,1358]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">C. nobiliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Otherwise both taxa are identical and lead me to synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC8FFE3FEC6FAB1FE1EFADE" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[314,416,1367,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="293" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="briseis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC8FFE3FEC6FAB1FE1EFADE" box="[314,416,1367,1390]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="293">C. briseis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the latter species.
</paragraph>
